This paper proposes a new model for natural language processing tasks, specifically improving upon the Bidirectional LSTM model. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also extensively evaluates the performance of the proposed model on various tasks, indicating a focus on machine learning and data analysis, which suggests categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions named entity recognition, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper also mentions text classification, which can be related to computer vision tasks, indicating a possible connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
